import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['age'] = pd.to_numeric(data['age'], errors='coerce')
    data = data.dropna(subset=['age'])
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='age', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['age'].median(), color='red', label='Median Age: {:.2f}'.format(data['age'].median()))
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['gender'].value_counts().plot(kind='pie', autopct='%1.1f%%', startangle=90, shadow=False, legend=True, fontsize=14)
    plt.title('What is the gender distribution of the deceased individuals?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['race'] = data['race'].fillna('Unknown')
    race_counts = data['race'].value_counts()
    race_counts = race_counts.reset_index()
    race_counts.columns = ['race', 'count']
    race_counts = race_counts.sort_values(by='count', ascending=False)
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.barplot(x='race', y='count', data=race_counts, palette='viridis')
    plt.title('What is the racial distribution of the deceased individuals?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Race')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    for i, v in enumerate(race_counts['count']):
        plt.text(i, v, str(v), ha='center', va='bottom', fontweight='bold')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
